ğŸš€Pika World Markets Update - Jan 9 2024ğŸš€ğŸ¢Technology stocks surged on Monday  and DJIA rose for a third consecutive day as investors await the upcoming inflation data  CPI on Thursday. CPI is expected to hit a low since March 2021  which could drive prospects for rate cuts that are hoped to come as early as March again  although this is less likely given a robust labour market.ğŸ”’Treasury yield remains steady  although paring some gains from the prior week after rising above 4%. There were several corporate news stories  so let us dive into them.ğŸ¯First on the list is Apple. The stock rose sharply after the company set a date for the sales of Vision Pro  which will be available in US retail stores and online stores starting Feb 2. Preorders are available on Jan 19  and the price is $3499.Wall Street has a modest expectation for shipment in 2024  but we are focusing on the "spatial computing" sphere  where it could help create a new product category just as it had when AirPods was launched in 2016.It is a space that investors are eyeing  given that Meta Platforms had struggled to find ground for its virtual and mixed-reality headsets under the brand Quest. Remember that Meta's Reality Lab is a money-losing business.âœˆï¸Boeing hits the headlines with concerns about its manufacturing quality after growing concerns about installation issues such as the door plug. Still  Wall Street takes some heat off the problem as it is expected that things could be resolved after the FAA give the final approval for operation upon reviewing the remedies and actions taken.Some have pointed to the issue as manufacturing rather than a more severe design issue  although more information is needed as the story develops.It is Jan 9  Tuesday  9 am in Singapore and 9 pm in New York. The market had a strong recovery  although still some distance from us offloading our positions. Given our loss-making hedge since before Christmas  I have decided to take up the loss to reduce some tiny positions while allowing the margin account to have a cushion for more downside risk.As spoken  my initial analysis is still for the S&P 500 to break a new high in January  although the odds are lower now.
